/*
  AtomS3R IMU calibration wizard (Accel + Gyro [+ optional Mag]) using imu_cal::* calibrators.

  GOALS (human-usable):
  - No “press screen” nonsense (many poses have screen down).
  - Big, plain-English pose instructions.
  - Slow flow: you get time to reposition every pose.
  - Won’t “loop instantly” because we force a reposition delay and we require STILLNESS
    before we even start collecting samples.
  - Shows WHY you’re stuck (stillness not reached, accepted=0, timeout, etc.)
  - Saves a CRC’d blob to NVS (Preferences namespace "imu_cal") and READS IT BACK to verify.
  - Status screen shows:
      * BLOB YES/NO
      * per-sensor ok flags
      * last failure reason (if any)

  NOTES:
  - Some AtomS3 variants have NO magnetometer. This wizard detects that and SKIPS mag.
  - For USB-C DOWN pose: you MUST unplug the USB cable. If the port can’t sit flat,
    rest the unit on two coins/spacers so the port points down without wobbling.

  REQUIREMENTS:
    - M5Unified library
    - ESP32 Arduino core (Preferences)
    - ArduinoEigenDense
    - CalibrateIMU_alt.h  (your imu_cal::AccelCalibrator/GyroCalibrator/MagCalibrator)

  Units:
    accel: m/s^2
    gyro:  rad/s
    mag:   uT
*/

